  "solution_steps": "Step 1: Rewrite each term as a fraction: (1 + 1/2) = 3/2, (1 + 1/3) = 4/3, (1 + 1/4) = 5/4, (1 + 1/5) = 6/5, (1 + 1/6) = 7/6, (1 + 1/7) = 8/7, (1 + 1/8) = 9/8, (1 + 1/9) = 10/9. \nStep 2: Multiply all fractions: (3/2) × (4/3) × (5/4) × (6/5) × (7/6) × (8/7) × (9/8) × (10/9). \nStep 3: Notice that the product telescopes, meaning nearly all numerator factors cancel with the denominators of the subsequent fraction, leaving just 10 in the numerator and 2 in the denominator. \nStep 4: Simplify the remaining fraction: 10/2 = 5.",
